  <p id="xdMxgS"><em>Ahsoka, </em>Disney’s next big Disney Plus <em>Star Wars</em> show, will now premiere on Tuesday nights at 9PM ET / 6PM PT, <a href="https://twitter.com/starwars/status/1692552080764887366">Disney announced on Friday</a>. That means the first two episodes of the show will now be available the evening of Tuesday, August 22nd.</p>
<p id="F1dWjJ">It’s only a slight shift from <em>Ahsoka</em>’s original premiere date of Wednesdays. But since Disney Plus shows typically come out in the middle of the night, this new air time might make episodes easier to watch the moment they debut.</p>
